│ The `VPUser` class defines the `getOperand` method, which retrieves an operand from the │
│ `Operands` vector. It asserts that the index is within bounds but does not check if the │
│ operand itself is null. This means that if a null operand is stored in the `Operands`   │
│ vector, it could propagate and cause issues later.                                      │
│                                                                                         │
│ To address this, I will add a null check for operands retrieved by `getOperand` in the  │
│ `computeCost` function of `VPPartialReductionRecipe`. This will ensure that null        │
│ operands are handled gracefully before being used.                                      │
│                                                                                         │
